div.p: RoutingKey: "url.clicked" Body (raw JSON): json { "event_type": "url.clicked", "event_id": "uuid-EID-001", "occurred_at": "2026-03-02T14:05:00Z", "correlation_id": "uuid-CORR-42", "short_code": "aB3xY9z", "user_id": "uuid-USER-7", "user_email": "alice@example.com", "ip_hash": "<sha256 from url-service>", "user_agent": "Mozilla/5.0 ...", "referer": "https://twitter.com" }
sql SELECT 1 FROM processed_events WHERE event_id = $1 -- "uuid-EID-001"
Note: analytics-service does NOT compute the IP hash. url-service already computed: sha256(raw_ip + CLICK_SALT) This service NEVER sees the raw IP address.
sql INSERT INTO clicks (short_code, clicked_at, ip_hash, user_agent, referer) VALUES ($1, $2, $3, $4, $5)
sql INSERT INTO processed_events (event_id) VALUES ($1) -- "uuid-EID-001" ON CONFLICT (event_id) DO NOTHING
sql SELECT COUNT(*) FROM clicks WHERE short_code = $1 -- "aB3xY9z"
